PERSONAL NOTES:


SD card reading: 
- Pi 5 already has that so its chill to do that 
- Use regular c++ file system commands to access stuff on sd card
- How do I know where the sd card has mounted?
- Do I need to use FATFS? 

Audio Files: 
- Audio files will be .WAV (PCM + header)
- PCM (pulse code modulation)
- Numbers that represent the samples over time
- Header
- Format of file
- Sampling rate of audio
- Bit width of each sample
- Number of channels
- libsndfile library
- C library for reading / writing audio files
- Takes many different audio file formats and is able to read them and save data from them all


Playing it out loud:
- Need to get audio out of speakers
- Would need to use a standard linux audio layer
- PortAudio
- Allows you to output audio onto the pi audio headphone jack

Actual Audio Filters:
- Volume Up - arm up
- Volume down - arm down
- Cut the bass - (high pass)
- Cut the treble (low pass)
- Reverb (comb)

For the interface:
- Dear ImGui

Architecture:
- Just have both programs act as separate programs
- They have shared memory
- Detecting a hand signal triggers calling a function

Files:

─ main.cpp (init everything, start the GUI)
─ audio_player.h / audio_player.cpp (portaudio and libsndfile) (gets samples & plays them)
─ dsp.h / dsp.cpp (take in floats, output other floats)
─ Makefile


